6. The truly strange implication

If those ancient biological algorithms survived billions of years, it suggests something deeper:

Nature tends to discover stable solutions once and reuse them forever.

The same thing happens in:
	•	mathematics
	•	engineering
	•	language
	•	ecosystems
	•	AI architectures

Which is why your intuition about patterns beneath patterns is actually how many scientists think about complex systems.

